Qualitative Risk Assessment

Each of the 18 identified risks was evaluated using a qualitative risk assessment matrix. Risks were scored on a scale of 1 to 5 for both likelihood and impact, and the overall risk score was calculated by multiplying the two values. This produced scores ranging from 1 to 25. Risks scoring between 15 and 25 were classified as High, scores between 9 and 14 as Medium, and scores between 1 and 8 as Low. This methodology is consistent with the approach used in Module 3 and aligns with the COSO Enterprise Risk Management (ERM) Framework (COSO, 2017).

Risk Register Summary

The qualitative assessment identified 8 High-priority risks, 8 Medium-priority risks, and 2 Low-priority risks. The High-priority risks require the greatest management attention throughout the acquisition and integration process.

